title: God Emperor
author: LeBassFreq
pages:
#- My beautiful Sareer. Once a mighty desert covering the planet; it is no more than a conservatory in this age, a group of scattered deserts surrounded by lush forest. I must spend my days either alone or here in what remains of dune, my lovely Sareer. The 
#- moisture irritates my
body, but this is how it must be; in order for my Golden Path to continue, in order for the survival of my children, of all human kind. What you wander through are the remains of Sietch Tabr, a once great hall of Fremen, ruled by the
#- Naib Stilgar and his wives. Onto it, centuries after Stilgar's death, I ordered the construction of a new Shield Wall to protect my city of Onn from the desert winds until plant life gained control of this planet. By the time that you read this, my great
#- wall will likely be not more than rubble, a fragment of the 200 meter-high marvel that it once was. Your finding this signifies only one thing; you were meant to come here. In these ruins hide a vast store of diamonds and emeralds, concealed after I took 
#- rule of the Imperium some 3500 standard years before I write this. I have lived a long life, those who I once loved come and go, I no longer hold attachments of the sort. Go now and find my treasure, you have surely earned it.
#- 